lead_paragraph: Ukraine will remain on the offensive this winter, retaking ground lost to the Russian invasion, Lloyd Austin, the U.S. secretary of defense, predicted yesterday. The U.S. and its allies will continue to supply Ukraine with the supplies needed to “regain its territory and to be effective on the battleground,” he said after a meeting of top global military officials, the U.S.-led Ukraine Defense Contact Group.
